.TH @PACKAGE@_exclude @FILE_SECTION@ 2011
.\"=========================================================
.\" NAME
.\"=========================================================
.SH NAME
\fB@PACKAGE@_exclude\fR \- IP Address exclusion file for @PACKAGE@
.\"=========================================================
.\" SYNTAX
.\"=========================================================
.SH SYNTAX
.nf
<\fIAddress\fR>

<\fIAddress\fR>/<\fIPrefix\fR>

# Comments
.fi
.\"=========================================================
.\" DESCRIPTION
.\"=========================================================
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fB@PACKAGE@\fR can be configured to ignore IP Addresses. The action
script will not be executed for hosts appearing in the
\fB@PACKAGE@_exclude\fR file. The \fIexclude\fR directive in
@PACKAGE@.conf(@FILE_SECTION@) is used to specify the file to be read
containing.
.P
It is possible to specify entire IP ranges using prefix length or
single IP addresses. Both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are supported.
.P
\fB@PACKAGE@\fR expects one IP address or range per line. Lines
starting with a '#' are ignored.
.P
If changes are made to the exclude file, sending \fISIGHUP\fR to
\fB@PACKAGE@\fR process causes \fB@PACKAGE@\fR to re-read the contents
of the file.
.\"=========================================================
.\" EXAMPLE
.\"=========================================================
.SH EXAMPLE

.nf
192.168.1.0/24
172.16.1.1
fd3e:be3e:ec34::/64

.fi

